05/08/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian-Montenegrin Minister for Human and Minority Rights Rasim Ljajic announced Monday (4 August) that six or seven more war crimes indictments would be issued for Serbian-Montenegrin citizens soon.
He said the war crimes tribunal is about to issue 35 indictments for suspects across the former Yugoslavia.
(Vecernje Novosti, Tanjug, BBC - 04/08/03)
